## What gets added (no existing code modified, no headers touched)

### 1. New file: `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3.jinja`

A Jinja template encoding the official Mistral Instruct v0.3 format:
- Pulls out a leading system message (if any) and prepends it to the **first** user turn, inside `[INST]`
- User turns: `[INST] {content} [/INST]`
- Assistant turns: ` {content}</s>`
- **Critically**: contains `[/INST]` but **not** `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` or `[TOOL_CALLS]` — the three signals used for detection

### 2. `common/chat.cpp` — two insertions

**A) Handler function** (insert before `namespace workaround {` at ~line 1519):
```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;
    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });
    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```
Simple content-only PEG parser — `</s>` is the EOS token and is stripped by the inference engine, so the parser just captures `rest()`.

**B) Detection block** (inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`, after the Ministral-3 block at ~line 1644):
```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v3 - [INST]/[/INST] format with system prepended to first user turn
// Distinguishes from Ministral 3 by the absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
if (src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[TOOL_CALLS]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```
| Condition | What it excludes |
|-----------|-----------------|
| `[/INST]` present | Positively identifies Mistral instruct family |
| `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent | Ministral-3 and v7/Devstral (already caught earlier or use different token) |
| `[TOOL_CALLS]` absent | Nemo and other tool-capable Mistral variants (need their own future handler) |

### 3. `tests/test-chat.cpp` — one new block (after Ministral-3 tests at ~line 1770)
